ZCZC EE47
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES ACROSS THE NITON AREA
BRINGING GENERALLY BENIGN CONDITIONS.
THIS RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE DOMINATES THE AREA THROUGHOUT THIS PERIOD
WITH SMALL CHANGES IN PRESSURE AND POSITION BRINGING STRG WINDS AT TIMES
BEFORE GIVING WAY TO AN INTENSE LOW OVER THE WEEKEND. OVERNIGHT THURSDAY
THE HIGH BUILDS BRINGING STRG WINDS TO SOLE LUNDY FASTNET IRISH SEA AND
SHANNON. DURING FRIDAY STRG WINDS PERSIST AS HIGH PRESSURE CONTINUES TO BUILD
AND SPREAD E TO WIGHT PORTLAND AND PLYMOUTH. LITTLE CHANGE EXP OVERNIGHT.
DURING SATURDAY STRG WINDS EASE ACROSS ALL AREAS EXCEPT SHANNON. OVERNIGHT
SATURDAY A NEW LOW DEVELOPING W OF UK WATERS MOVS E BRINGING GALES TO LUNDY
FASTNET IRISH SEA AND SHANNON BY SUNDAY MORNING AND STRG WINDS TO THE ENGLISH
CHANNEL. DURING SUNDAY THE LOW MOVS E WITH GALES SPREADING TO THE ENGLISH
CHANNEL. LITTLE CHANGE ELSEWHERE
